e-Based Practice      Citation Styles      Practice-Based Resources     Toggle Dropdown     Mobile Resources @ UIC    Continuing Education & Certification    Patient Education    Nursing Career Resources      Tutorials      Quad Cities/Springfield      Course Guides     Toggle Dropdown     NUPR 539/540/541    NURS 204    NURS 254    NURS 304    NURS 515/516    NURS 532    NURS 540    NUSP 515    NUSP 534    NUSP 535    DNP Project Guide    Salud    School Nursing                Welcome to the Nursing Guide     This guide is the main library guide for nursing. This guide has links to resources such as databases, evidence-based practice resources, patient education, and more. Please contact your Nursing Library Liaison from your campus if you need help along the way. We can meet with you in person or online.                 Quick Links-Library Resources      Catalog for UIC Library     CARLI I-Share Catalog       CINAHL Plus with Full Text   more...  less...   The Cumulative Index to Nursing and Allied Health (CINAHL) database provides authoritative coverage of the literature related to nursing and allied health.    Cochrane Library   more...  less...   The Cochrane Library is a collection of databases that contain independent evidence on which to base clinical treatment decisions. * Cochrane Reviews, aka Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews (CDSR) * Other Reviews, aka Database of Abstracts of Reviews of Effects (DARE) * Clinical Trials; aka Cochrane Central Register of Controlled Trials (CENTRAL) * Methods Studies, aka Cochrane Methodology Register (CMR) * Technology Assessments, aka Health Technology Assessment Database (HTA) * Economic Evaluations, aka National Health Service (NHS) Economic Evaluation Database (NHSEED) * Cochrane Groups, aka About the Cochrane Collaboration      E-books       Need to find a journal?      EBSCO Mobile    more...  less...   EBSCO Mobile can be used on several smartphones, especially through the more popular ones:  * Android * BlackBerry * Dell Axim * iPhone * Palm 750    HAPI (Health and Psychosocial Instruments)     Interlibrary Loan/ILLiad     MEDLINE via Ovid     MEDLINE via PubMed@UIC    more...  less...   MEDLINE is the National Library of Medicine's premier bibliographic database covering the fields of medicine, nursing, dentistry, veterinary medicine, the health care system, and the preclinical sciences. MEDLINE contains bibliographic citations and author abstracts from more than 4,600 biomedical journals published in the United States and 70 other countries. The database contains over 12 million citations dating back to the mid-1960's. Coverage is worldwide, but most records are from English-language sources or have English abstracts.      Nursing Reference Center Plus   more...  less...   This database complements CINAHL; providing the most recent clinical evidence to nurses and other health care professionals, directly at the point-of-care.    PsycINFO   more...  less...   PsycINFO contains bibliographic citations and abstracts from materials in the field of psychology and the psychological aspects of related disciplines, such as medicine, psychiatry, nursing, sociology, education, pharmacology, physiology, linguistics, anthropology, business, and law.  Updated weekly.      RefWorks: Build a Bibliography                  Nursing Library Liaisons         Chicago  Graduate Nursing  Rebecca Raszewski (312) 996-2759  raszewr1@uic.edu Skype: raszewr1  Pre-Licensure & Graduate Entry Nursing  Annie Nickum (312) 413-2464  anicku2@uic.edu  Schedule Appointment     Rockford  Cynthia Reynolds  (815) 395-5658 cmreynol@uic.edu      Peoria & Quad Cities  Emily Johnson-Barlow (309) 671-8490  lib-pref@uic.edu    Urbana & Springfield  Ryan Rafferty (217) 244-0607  lib-lhsu-ref@uic.edu                        In Person and Online Library Workshops     Please register for these workshops through the UIC Library Events calendar.                  Next: Where to Find... >>        Last Updated:  May 8, 20